{"number":57684,"title":"New foundry *_call/*_call_output items can&#39;t be sent as Responses input; Conversations API returns undocumented remote_function_call instead","body":"# [BUG] Foundry agent tool call types have dual discriminator and block stateless multi-turn replay

## Library name and version

Azure.AI.Projects 2.0.0-beta.2 (transitively pulls Azure.AI.Extensions.OpenAI 2.0.0-beta.1, OpenAI 2.9.1)

## Describe the bug

Two related issues with how Azure-specific agent tool call types (e.g. `openapi_call`) surface through the Responses and Conversations APIs:

### 1. Stateless multi-turn replay fails for Azure tool types

When using `ProjectResponsesClient` with an agent that has Azure-specific tools (OpenAPI, AI Search, Bing Grounding), `ResponseResult.OutputItems` contains items with `&#34;type&#34;: &#34;openapi_call&#34;`. Attempting to replay these as `InputItems` in a follow-up request (stateless multi-turn) results in HTTP 400:

```
HTTP 400 (invalid_request_error: invalid_value)
Parameter: input[1]
Invalid value: &#39;openapi_call&#39;. Supported values are: &#39;apply_patch_call&#39;, &#39;apply_patch_call_output&#39;,
&#39;code_interpreter_call&#39;, &#39;compaction&#39;, &#39;computer_call&#39;, &#39;computer_call_output&#39;, &#39;custom_tool_call&#39;,
&#39;custom_tool_call_output&#39;, &#39;file_search_call&#39;, &#39;function_call&#39;, &#39;function_call_output&#39;,
&#39;image_generation_call&#39;, &#39;item_reference&#39;, &#39;local_shell_call&#39;, &#39;local_shell_call_output&#39;,
&#39;mcp_approval_request&#39;, &#39;mcp_approval_response&#39;, &#39;mcp_call&#39;, &#39;mcp_list_tools&#39;, &#39;message&#39;,
&#39;reasoning&#39;, &#39;shell_call&#39;, &#39;shell_call_output&#39;, &#39;tool_search_call&#39;, &#39;tool_search_output&#39;,
and &#39;web_search_call&#39;.
```

This forces users into server-managed state (`PreviousResponseId` or Conversations API) — there&#39;s no way to do stateless multi-turn with Azure-specific tools.

### 2. Dual discriminator: Conversations API returns undocumented type

The same logical operation (an OpenAPI tool call) surfaces with different `type` values depending on the API:

| API | JSON `type` value | SDK deserialization result |
|---|---|---|
| Responses API `output[]` | `openapi_call` | [`InternalUnknownItemResource`](https://github.com/openai/openai-dotnet/blob/[REDACTED]/src/Generated/Models/Responses/ResponseItem.Serialization.cs#L158) (OpenAI SDK doesn&#39;t know it) |
| Conversations API items | `remote_function_call` (with `&#34;label&#34;: &#34;remote_openapi&#34;`) | [`UnknownAgentResponseItem`](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/[REDACTED]/sdk/ai/Azure.AI.Extensions.OpenAI/src/Generated/Models/AgentResponseItem.Serialization.cs#L226) (Azure SDK doesn&#39;t know it either) |

`remote_function_call` is **not in the published [Foundry OpenAPI spec](https://github.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/tree/[REDACTED]/specification/ai-foundry/data-plane/Foundry/openapi3)** (`microsoft-foundry-openapi3.json` has `openapi_call` but no `remote_function_call`), yet the Conversations endpoint returns it. The [`AgentResponseItem` deserializer](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/[REDACTED]/sdk/ai/Azure.AI.Extensions.OpenAI/src/Generated/Models/AgentResponseItem.Serialization.cs#L226) has a case for `openapi_call` but not `remote_function_call`, so Conversations items with tool calls fall through to `UnknownAgentResponseItem`.

## Expected behavior

1. **Stateless replay should work**: `OutputItems` from a Responses API call should be directly replayable as `InputItems` in a subsequent request without requiring `PreviousResponseId`. The server should accept `openapi_call` as input.

2. **Consistent discriminator**: The same tool call should use the same `type` discriminator across both Responses and Conversations APIs, matching the published OpenAPI spec. `GetProjectConversationItemsAsync` should return typed `AgentResponseItem` subtypes (e.g. `OpenAPIToolCall`), not `UnknownAgentResponseItem`.

## Actual behavior

1. Replaying `OutputItems` as `InputItems` → HTTP 400 rejecting `openapi_call` as input type.
2. Conversations API returns `remote_function_call` (undocumented) instead of `openapi_call`, which deserializes as `UnknownAgentResponseItem`.

## Reproduction Steps

Minimal repro for issue 1 (stateless replay failure):

```csharp
using Azure.Identity;
using Azure.AI.Projects;
using Azure.AI.Projects.Agents;
using Azure.AI.Extensions.OpenAI;
using OpenAI.Responses;

var projectEndpoint = &#34;&#34;;
var modelDeploymentName = &#34;gpt-4o-mini&#34;;
AIProjectClient projectClient = new(new Uri(projectEndpoint), new DefaultAzureCredential());

// Create agent with OpenAPI tool
string specPath = Path.Combine(AppContext.BaseDirectory, &#34;weather_openapi.json&#34;);
OpenApiFunctionDefinition toolDef = new(
    name: &#34;get_weather&#34;,
    specificationBytes: BinaryData.FromBytes(File.ReadAllBytes(specPath)),
    authentication: new OpenAPIAnonymousAuthenticationDetails());
OpenAPITool openapiTool = new(toolDef);

PromptAgentDefinition agentDef = new(model: modelDeploymentName)
{
    Instructions = &#34;You are a helpful assistant.&#34;,
    Tools = { openapiTool }
};
AgentVersion agentVersion = projectClient.Agents.CreateAgentVersion(&#34;myAgent&#34;, new(agentDef));

ProjectResponsesClient responseClient = projectClient.OpenAI.GetProjectResponsesClientForAgent(
    new AgentReference(agentVersion.Name, agentVersion.Version));

// First request works
ResponseResult response = responseClient.CreateResponse(&#34;What is the weather in Seattle?&#34;);
Console.WriteLine(response.GetOutputText());

// Stateless follow-up: replay OutputItems as InputItems → HTTP 400
var opts = new CreateResponseOptions();
opts.InputItems.Add(ResponseItem.CreateUserMessageItem(&#34;What is the weather in Seattle?&#34;));
foreach (var item in response.OutputItems)
    opts.InputItems.Add(item);  // Contains openapi_call items
opts.InputItems.Add(ResponseItem.CreateUserMessageItem(&#34;What about Portland?&#34;));
ResponseResult followUp = responseClient.CreateResponse(opts); // THROWS: HTTP 400

// Cleanup
projectClient.Agents.DeleteAgentVersion(agentVersion.Name, agentVersion.Version);
```

Minimal repro for issue 2 (dual discriminator — `remote_function_call` instead of `openapi_call`):

```csharp
using Azure.Identity;
using Azure.AI.Projects;
using Azure.AI.Projects.Agents;
using Azure.AI.Extensions.OpenAI;
using OpenAI.Responses;

var projectEndpoint = &#34;&#34;;
var modelDeploymentName = &#34;gpt-4o-mini&#34;;
AIProjectClient projectClient = new(new Uri(projectEndpoint), new DefaultAzureCredential());

// Create agent with OpenAPI tool (same setup as issue 1)
string specPath = Path.Combine(AppContext.BaseDirectory, &#34;weather_openapi.json&#34;);
OpenApiFunctionDefinition toolDef = new(
    name: &#34;get_weather&#34;,
    specificationBytes: BinaryData.FromBytes(File.ReadAllBytes(specPath)),
    authentication: new OpenAPIAnonymousAuthenticationDetails());
OpenAPITool openapiTool = new(toolDef);

PromptAgentDefinition agentDef = new(model: modelDeploymentName)
{
    Instructions = &#34;You are a helpful assistant.&#34;,
    Tools = { openapiTool }
};
AgentVersion agentVersion = projectClient.Agents.CreateAgentVersion(
    agentName: &#34;myAgent&#34;, options: new AgentVersionCreationOptions(agentDef));

// Create a conversation and send a query via Responses API
var conversationsClient = projectClient.OpenAI.GetProjectConversationsClient();
ProjectConversation conversation = await conversationsClient.CreateProjectConversationAsync();

ProjectResponsesClient responseClient = projectClient.OpenAI.GetProjectResponsesClientForAgent(
    new AgentReference(agentVersion.Name, agentVersion.Version));
CreateResponseOptions opts = new()
{
    InputItems = { ResponseItem.CreateUserMessageItem(&#34;What is the weather in Seattle?&#34;) },
};
opts.AgentConversationId = conversation.Id;
ResponseResult response = responseClient.CreateResponse(opts);

// Retrieve conversation items — tool calls come back as &#34;remote_function_call&#34;
await foreach (AgentResponseItem item in conversationsClient.GetProjectConversationItemsAsync(conversation.Id))
{
    // All items are UnknownAgentResponseItem — none resolve to OpenApiToolCall
    // because the server returns &#34;type&#34;: &#34;remote_function_call&#34; (not &#34;openapi_call&#34;)
    Console.WriteLine($&#34;{item.GetType().Name}&#34;);
    // Prints: UnknownAgentResponseItem (×4)
}

// Cleanup
await conversationsClient.DeleteConversationAsync(conversation.Id);
projectClient.Agents.DeleteAgentVersion(agentVersion.Name, agentVersion.Version);
```

## Environment

- Windows 11, .NET 10.0
- Azure.AI.Projects 2.0.0-beta.2
- Azure.AI.Extensions.OpenAI 2.0.0-beta.1 (transitive)
- OpenAI 2.9.1 (transitive)
